item.title: Hezbollah leader Nasrallah killed: Israeli PM Netanyahu says 'settled score'
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu declared that Israel had "settled the score" with the assassination of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah in a Beirut airstrike. Netanyahu highlighted Nasrallah's role in numerous deaths, including Americans and French citizens. He asserted that eliminating Nasrallah was essential for achieving Israel's objectives and facilitating the return of hostages captured by Hamas.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Nasrallah, Hezbollah chief for 32 years, killed in Israel airstrike
item.description: Hezbollah confirmed that its leader Hassan Nasrallah was killed in an Israeli airstrike in Beirut. The strike also resulted in the deaths of other Hezbollah commanders and an Iranian general. Israel announced plans to intensify its operations against Hezbollah, leading to substantial displacement among Lebanese and Israelis amid escalating tensions.

item.title: 'More high profile than...': Attorney says Diddy's secret tapes being sold in Hollywood
item.description: ​“There already have been tapes leaking around Hollywood being shopped around, but one particular person contacted me to shop a particular video,” Mitchell-Kidd said. “I can tell the video was pornographic. This was in his Atlanta home, and it does seem like the person isn’t looking into the video. To me, it doesn’t seem like that person knows they’re being videotaped.”
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Measure of justice...': US President Joe Biden on Hezbollah leader Nasrallah's death
item.description: US President Joe Biden termed the death of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah in an Israeli airstrike as 'a measure of justice.' The incident follows Hezbollah's engagement in the conflict post-Hamas’s October 7, 2023, attack on Israel. Biden reiterated US support for Israel and highlighted ongoing diplomatic efforts to de-escalate tensions.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Meghan Markle sends emails to her staff at 5 am but is kind enough to...
item.description: ​"My working day may not be your working day. Please do not feel obliged to reply to this email outside your normal working hours," Meghan writes this in her mails. Her staff claimed she is flexible and fair-minded like that. Meghan has around 16 staffers working for production on various Netflix projects, podcasts, the Archewell Foundation, and communications. Meghan shares credit and writes personal email thanking her staff for their contribution, an ex-staffer said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Lavrov warns against 'fighting to victory' with nuclear power, blasts western nations at UN
item.description: Sergey Lavrov, Russia's foreign minister, warned against efforts to defeat a nuclear power like Russia, addressing the Ukraine conflict at the UN General Assembly. He criticised Western actions and called Zelenskyy's peace formula a doomed ultimatum. The nuclear threat has been significant since Russia invaded Ukraine in February 2022.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pakistan: Imran Khan's party yet to get permission for Sunday rally
Laura Loomer now attacks Kamala Harris on religion. 'Has anyone asked her?'
item.description: Far-right activist Laura Loomer questioned Kamala Harris' religion after she confirmed she would skip the AI Smith dinner on October 17. Loomer's controversial remarks about Harris' ethnicity were condemned by Republicans and distanced by Donald Trump. Harris has a unique religious identity, having been introduced to both Hinduism and Christianity, as she said earlier.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Hurricane Helene traps families, leaves North Carolina mountain towns in ruins
item.description: Hurricane Helene's impact on North Carolina's mountain regions has left families isolated due to landslides and flooding. The storm made landfall in Florida and caused at least 52 fatalities across five states. Major roadways are closed, with preliminary damage estimates ranging from $15 billion to $26 billion.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Israeli PM Netanyahu presents maps at UN, labels India a 'blessing' and Iran a 'curse'
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu addressed the UN General Assembly, displaying two maps one as a "blessing" and the other as a "curse. He described the map titled 'The Curse' featured Iran, Iraq, Syria, and Yemen colored in black, while the map labeled 'The Blessing' highlighted Egypt, Sudan, Saudi Arabia, and India in green.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: This Republican politician 'borrows' wife and children for photoshoot
item.description: Republican Derrick Anderson, running for Virginia's seventh congressional district, faced backlash after using a friend's family in a campaign photoshoot. Anderson, who is engaged and childless, defended the footage as featuring supporters. This incident sparked social media criticism and highlighted GOP efforts to attract female voters amid ongoing abortion debates.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Queen Camilla does not want King Charles to meet Prince Harry because...
item.description: ​The King sent a birthday wish to Prince Harry as the prince turned 40 hinting at a thawing of their relationship caused by the hurt that Prince Harry delivered by badmouthing the Royal Family and then quitting the royal responsibilities. But a public birthday wish is the most King Charles would do, a meeting may not happen but nobody is ruling out a meeting as well.

item.title: Titan sub tragedy: Coast guard hearings reveal new insights
Video: How Israel executed operation 'New Order' to kill Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah in Beirut
item.description: Israel executed airstrikes on Hezbollah positions in Lebanon, targeting over 140 sites and killing multiple commanders, including leader Hassan Nasrallah. Iranian deputy commander Abbas Nilforushan was also among the casualties. This week has seen one of the deadliest escalations since the 2006 war between Israel and Hezbollah, with over 700 deaths reported.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Mass shootings in South Africa leaves seventeen dead in same town
item.description: Seventeen people were killed in two separate mass shootings on Friday night in Lusikisiki, South Africa. The victims included 15 women and two men. “A manhunt has been launched to apprehend those behind these heinous killings,” Brig. Athlenda Mathe said. These incidents underscore South Africa's high homicide rate and increasing frequency of mass shootings.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Tulsi Gabbard calls Kamala Harris shameless as VP inspects US-Mexico border: 'No conscience'
item.description: Kamala Harris visited Arizona's border with Mexico for the first time since becoming the Democratic presidential nominee, pledging to secure the border and reform immigration. Critics, including Tulsi Gabbard and JD Vance, dismissed it as a photo op and questioned why she hasn't already addressed these issues as Vice President.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris' sister says she will call her 'Madam President' when she's elected, 'Until then...'
item.description: 57-year-old Maya, a lawyer and a public policy advisor, said she is very proud to be part of Kamala Harris' presidential campaign and the feeling is extraordinary, electric. "I am just so proud to be able to be out there in these states encouraging people to knock on every door, call every voter, text their friends and family members between now and Election Day, to really have those personal conversations that help people learn who Kamala is, what she's fighting for, why they believe in her," Maya told People magazine.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: RFK Jr and Olivia Nuzzi had 'incredible' FaceTime sex: Report
item.description: The new revelation that they had FaceTime sex is part of the charges that the two camps are lobbing at each other. Sources told Page Six that Nuzzi was first disgusted by Kennedy Jr after he made a clumsy pass at her. But then Kennedy Jr "love bombed" her which went well and Nuzzi was "madly in love" with him. There were long calls, endless texts and virtual sex which ruined Nuzzi's relationship with her fiance Ryan Lizza, who was a journalist with Politico.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Drugged, raped for years': Sean 'Diddy' Combs faces new sexual assault lawsuit
item.description: Sean 'Diddy' Combs, detained in Brooklyn's Metropolitan Detention Centre, faces fresh sexual assault allegations from a former model who claims he drugged and raped her since 2021. The lawsuit adds to existing complaints against him. Combs denies most allegations and remains incarcerated without bail as investigations continue.
